to get started install the SCSS compiler in VSCode, create a .scss file, & hit 'watch' to activate real time compilation 
if there's a syntax error in the .scss file it should show up in the VSCode terminal 


$dark_green = #CCA135;                      // declare & use variables. variables can be global or local 

body {
    background-color: $dark_green; 

    header, p {                             // you can nest elements. selector lists are compatible with nesting 
        background-color: white;
    }
}
